Generate gpg public key:
gpg2 --full-gen-key
notice: real name and email should be: "minliu" and "wzygzlm@gmail.com"

How to generate the password gpg file:
echo "YourPassword" | gpg2 --encrypt --recipient "Your Name" -o ~/.mail-ini-passwd.gpg

Refer to:
fkoehler's blog: Encrypt OfflineIMAP and msmtp password with GnuPG
http://f-koehler.github.io/posts/2015-03-17-offlineimap-msmtp-gnupg.html
